About AMG 


AMG OverviewPhilosophyHistoryClientsProductsAMG FundsAMG Wealth PartnersAffiliatesManagement Team





Back to AMG AffiliatesHarding Loevner LPInvestment DisciplineHarding Loevner manages global and non-US equity portfolios following a consistent philosophy focused on long-term investment in growing companies with high-quality fundamentals. The firm invests only in businesses that are skillfully managed, financially strong, benefit from competitive advantages in their industries, and are well positioned for sustainable growth. Portfolio holdings are researched and valued by a team of analysts using a disciplined process that combines in-depth study of individual companies and global analysis of their industries’ competitive structures. Harding Loevner believes well-diversified portfolios of the stocks of companies meeting its quality-growth criteria, purchased at reasonable prices, offer superior risk-adjusted returns over the long term.The FirmFounded in 1989, Harding Loevner offers six primary investment strategies: Global Equity, International Equity, International Equity Research, International Small Companies Equity, Emerging Markets Equity, and Frontier Emerging Markets Equity. They are available through a variety of investment vehicles: separate accounts; US-based Harding, Loevner Funds, Inc.; Collective Investment Trusts; Ireland-based Harding Loevner Funds plc; and Australian Unit Trusts. A number of leading sponsored wealth management programs also offer the firm’s strategies. Harding Loevner serves a diverse global client base that includes foundations, endowments, pension plans, private family offices, and individuals.Contact Information400 Crossing Boulevard,  4th FloorBridgewater, New Jersey 08807+1 (908)  218-7900www.hardingloevner.com




